//env-cmd

//env-cmd is a utility that allows you to set environment variables from a specified file before running a command. 
//It makes it easy to load environment variables from a .env file into your Node.js
// application without needing to manually configure them within your code.

//This is particularly useful for managing different environments (like development, testing, and production)
// where you might have different configurations. For example, you can have .env.dev for development and .env for production.

//-f
// -f flag specifies the file from which to load environment variables.  